window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>In Knuckle Sandwich, years of drought come to a crashing end, but when it rains in New York, people get wet -- when it rains in L.A., people get killed. Ne’er-do-well punk rocker, Nick Paras accidentally becomes a private detective and has to find a missing goth girl. From ivory office towers to no-name clubs, the rain slick streets of Los Angeles won’t give Rachael up without a fight. Her family wants Nick to find her. But someone wants to kill him for trying.</p> <p>Justin DiPego says: “I want to take people into parts of the city they’ve never seen, or maybe only think they know, and shine a flashlight shaking with adrenaline into the dark corners.\"</p> <p>DiPego loves Los Angeles, and the city itself is a character in his stories, sometimes as a friend, as a neutral observer, and sometimes as an antagonist, because LA doesn’t always love you back.</p>"; 
